.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::RelayInfo \- NIP\-11 relay information document
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::RelayInfo;
\&
\&    # Build a relay information document
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->new(
\&        name           => \*(AqMy Relay\*(Aq,
\&        description    => \*(AqA relay for everyone\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey         => $admin_pubkey,
\&        self           => $relay_pubkey,
\&        contact        => \*(Aqmailto:admin@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        supported_nips => [1, 9, 11, 42, 44],
\&        software       => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/relay\*(Aq,
\&        version        => \*(Aq1.0.0\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Serialize to JSON
\&    my $json = $info\->to_json;
\&
\&    # Parse a relay info document (e.g. from an HTTP response)
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->from_json($json);
\&    say $info\->name;
\&    say join(\*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$info\->supported_nips});
\&
\&    # Generate an HTTP response with CORS headers
\&    my $http_response = $info\->to_http_response;
\&
\&    # Set on a relay to enable NIP\-11
\&    use Net::Nostr::Relay;
\&    my $relay = Net::Nostr::Relay\->new(
\&        relay_info => $info,
\&    );
\&    $relay\->start(\*(Aq127.0.0.1\*(Aq, 8080);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-11 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/11.md>,
the relay information document. This is a JSON document served over HTTP at the
same URI as the relay\*(Aqs WebSocket endpoint. Clients request it with an
\&\f(CW\*(C`Accept: application/nostr+json\*(C'\fR header.
.PP
When a \f(CW\*(C`relay_info\*(C'\fR is set on a Net::Nostr::Relay, the relay will
automatically serve the document in response to HTTP requests with the
correct Accept header, and handle CORS preflight OPTIONS requests.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 10
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->new(
\&        name             => \*(AqMy Relay\*(Aq,
\&        description      => \*(AqA relay for everyone\*(Aq,
\&        banner           => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/banner.jpg\*(Aq,
\&        icon             => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/icon.png\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey           => $admin_pubkey_hex,
\&        self             => $relay_pubkey_hex,
\&        contact          => \*(Aqmailto:admin@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        supported_nips   => [1, 9, 11],
\&        software         => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/relay\*(Aq,
\&        version          => \*(Aq1.0.0\*(Aq,
\&        terms_of_service => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/tos\*(Aq,
\&        limitation       => { max_subscriptions => 50 },
\&        payments_url     => \*(Aqhttps://example.com/pay\*(Aq,
\&        fees             => { admission => [{ amount => 1000, unit => \*(Aqmsats\*(Aq }] },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
All fields are optional and may be omitted. Croaks on unknown arguments.
The \f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR field SHOULD be less than 30 characters. The \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR field is
the administrative contact pubkey. The \f(CW\*(C`self\*(C'\fR field is the relay\*(Aqs own
pubkey. \f(CW\*(C`supported_nips\*(C'\fR is an arrayref of integer NIP numbers.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`limitation\*(C'\fR hashref may contain any of the following keys:
.PP
.Vb 10
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->new(
\&        limitation => {
\&            max_message_length   => 16384,
\&            max_subscriptions    => 300,
\&            max_limit            => 5000,
\&            max_subid_length     => 100,
\&            max_event_tags       => 100,
\&            max_content_length   => 8196,
\&            min_pow_difficulty   => 30,
\&            auth_required        => \e1,
\&            payment_required     => \e1,
\&            restricted_writes    => \e1,
\&            created_at_lower_limit => 31536000,
\&            created_at_upper_limit => 3,
\&            default_limit        => 500,
\&        },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`fees\*(C'\fR hashref maps fee types to arrayrefs of fee entries. Each fee
entry has \f(CW\*(C`amount\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`unit\*(C'\fR keys, and optionally \f(CW\*(C`period\*(C'\fR (for
subscriptions) or \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR (for per\-kind publication fees):
.PP
.Vb 10
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->new(
\&        payments_url => \*(Aqhttps://my\-relay/payments\*(Aq,
\&        fees => {
\&            admission    => [{ amount => 1000000, unit => \*(Aqmsats\*(Aq }],
\&            subscription => [{ amount => 5000000, unit => \*(Aqmsats\*(Aq,
\&                               period => 2592000 }],
\&            publication  => [{ kinds => [4], amount => 100,
\&                               unit => \*(Aqmsats\*(Aq }],
\&        },
\&    );
.Ve
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS from_json
.IX Subsection "from_json"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->from_json($json_string);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a JSON relay information document. Unknown fields are ignored per spec.
.PP
.Vb 7
\&    use HTTP::Tiny;
\&    my $resp = HTTP::Tiny\->new\->get($relay_url, {
\&        headers => { Accept => \*(Aqapplication/nostr+json\*(Aq },
\&    });
\&    die "Failed to fetch relay info: $resp\->{status}"
\&        unless $resp\->{success};
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->from_json($resp\->{content});
.Ve
.SS cors_preflight_response
.IX Subsection "cors_preflight_response"
.Vb 1
\&    my $http = Net::Nostr::RelayInfo\->cors_preflight_response;
.Ve
.PP
Returns an HTTP 204 response string with CORS headers for handling
OPTIONS preflight requests. May be called as a class method or a
function \-\- the invocant is not used.
.SH METHODS
.IX Header "METHODS"
.SS to_json
.IX Subsection "to_json"
.Vb 1
\&    my $json = $info\->to_json;
.Ve
.PP
Serializes the relay information document to a JSON string. Only fields
that have been set are included.
.SS to_http_response
.IX Subsection "to_http_response"
.Vb 1
\&    my $http = $info\->to_http_response;
.Ve
.PP
Returns a complete HTTP 200 response string with the JSON body,
\&\f(CW\*(C`Content\-Type: application/nostr+json\*(C'\fR, and the required CORS headers
(\f(CW\*(C`Access\-Control\-Allow\-Origin\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`Access\-Control\-Allow\-Headers\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`Access\-Control\-Allow\-Methods\*(C'\fR).
